$interpreted: : Kingdom of the Sun Calendar, year 189
Sunshine Infantry Soldier: How does it look, Captain Lucien? Did you see any monsters?
Fredrica: I didn't even see a shadow~
Fredrica: Ahhh~The monsters must value their beauty sleep, just like me~
Sunshine Infantry Soldier: Eh...I'm pretty sure it's because they got sucked into the void...
Sunshine Infantry Soldier: In any case, they returned to Atlas within the expected time, so that's good. It's just about time to report our results to General Levon.
Fredrica: ——WAIT!
Sunshine Infantry Soldier: Captain Lucien?
Fredrica: Monsters! A group of monsters is headed for the village!
Sunshine Infantry Soldier: Bu-Bu-But the Rune Sorcerer said that the void is in a cycle of inhalation, there's no way there are monsters!
Fredrica: Leave that up to the nerds! If you don't pick up a weapon, you're going to be the one getting gobbled up!
Fredrica: My God...look how many of them there are...
Fredrica: ——Get to base camp and call for reinforcements! Run!!!
Charle: Thank you so much, General, for allowing the Academy to follow the army and take notes on your operations.
Dylan: The feeling is mutual, sir.
Dylan: We must thank the Academy for providing us with records on the patterns of inhalation and exhalation exhibited by the void.
Fredrica: The Academy got it all wrong! The monsters are coming!
Dylan: What'd she say!?
Fredrica: Bumblefritters! We can't hold 'em off and we can't take 'em out...
Charle: Let us give it a try!
Charle: What the...? The records all indicate that it's in a cycle of inhalation. Yet, there are more monsters now than during the exhalation cycle.
Dylan: ——Sound the alarm!
Dylan: Headmaster Charle, Captain Lucien, and I will hold them off. The rest of you get to the village as quick as possible and tell the villagers to evacuate!
Charle: Students and teachers, assist the troops. We need to get those villagers out of there!
Fredrica: *sigh*...all this running around is so not woke...
Fredrica: Now I've got to act even angrier~
Fredrica: How am I gonna find a hot stud with all this crap going on??
Charle: Hehe...Miss Lucien hasn't changed a bit.
Dylan: ...Headmaster Charle, I may not be a scholar, but——
Charle: I know what you're wondering, General. But I can assure you that the Academy's calculations are correct.
Charle: The only reasonable explanation is that there have been changes in the void's cycles.
Dylan: That's what I was thinking. It looks like we'll have to bother the Academy for a new theory to explain what's happening.
Charle: ......
Dylan: Headmaster Charle?
Charle: If there is indeed a new theory for this phenomenon, then the Academy will do it's best.
Charle: But, if we're mistaken...
Messenger: Ge-General Levon! It doesn't look good!
Dylan: Speak!
Messenger: It's not just happening here! There are monsters in the neighboring village as well!
Messenger: The villagers didn't have time to escape. The men are keeping them at bay...but they can't hold on for much longer!
Dylan: Take me there!
Dylan: Soldiers of the Kingdom! Protect the retreating villagers!
Charle: We'll help cover them!
Charle: This way! Mrs. Lucien, you take that side over there!
Fredrica: Hey, look at that super cute boy over there! What's wrong!?
Charle: He's injured...oh, no...is this the void disease?
Dylan: Be careful!?

Young Boy: Owww! My eye!
There's something...petals!?
Capitol Soldier: ...Princess...
Capitol Soldier: ...Why...why...? You are...our princess...
Capitol Soldier: Why...would you do this...?
Capitol Soldier: ...All of this...was your doing?
Capitol Soldier: ...Princess......Angelia...
